# Options Zone Rules

## Purpose
Settings page that automatically renders all feature settings from schemas.

## Key Files
- `options.html` - Options page structure
- `options.ts` - Main options logic
- `options.css` - Options page styles
- `components/` - Reusable setting components

## Patterns
- Automatically load all features and render their settings schemas
- Use `renderFeatureSettings()` from shared utils
- Settings are rendered declaratively from feature schemas
- Search/filter functionality for finding settings

## Common Tasks
- Load all features to get their schemas
- Render settings using `renderFeatureSettings()`
- Handle search/filter
- Real-time updates when settings change

## What NOT to Do
- Don't manually create settings UI - use schemas
- Don't hardcode feature settings
- Don't forget to handle settings validation

## References
- See `src/shared/utils/settings-renderer.ts` for rendering utilities
- See `src/shared/types/settings-ui.ts` for schema types

